column4: I'm having problem with archive manager. It won't extract my rar fles. Archive not supported it says.
it gives huge amount of hits.
it's in Debian, maybe you don't have all the repos like multiverse/universe?
when's the late time you ran ``apt-get update'' manually?
oh, amd64, that might be why
I have an amd64 system at home, and that hasn't been the case for me
there's still some stuff that won't compile for one reason
you can try compiling it yourself and using checkinstall to install it
or... try looking at the config for archive manager, maybe you can tell it what program to use for rar
you could look at the ChangeLog for archive manager
